            <title>[JDK-8303486] [REDO] Update ProcessTools.startProcess(...) to exit early if process exit before linePredicate is printed.</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8303486</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>It is the 2nd attempt to fix &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8303133&quot; title=&quot;Update ProcessTools.startProcess(...) to exit early if process exit before linePredicate is printed.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8303133&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8303133&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Update ProcessTools.startProcess(...) to exit early if process exit before linePredicate is printed.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The first fix failed because it run &lt;br/&gt;
Utils.waitForCondition(BooleanSupplier condition, long timeout, long sleepTime) { ..}&lt;br/&gt;
with 0 as no timeout and not -1 as required.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Might it is needed to update waitForCondition to us 0 for this to be java compliant.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
the additional diff is:&lt;br/&gt;
diff --git a/test/lib/jdk/test/lib/process/ProcessTools.java b/test/lib/jdk/test/lib/process/ProcessTools.java&lt;br/&gt;
